kenny wrote:
&gt; Heritrix installation is fine. Profiles and setting done according to
&gt; the user manual. After I create job, it finishs immediately. The crawl
&gt; report shows that it crawl 0 Bytes, and seed report shows failed to
&gt; crawl seed. The crawl logs shows nothing crawl, and the other error
&gt; logs are empty. The DNS networking setting of the computer is OK. PLZ
&gt; help me out with this problem. Many thanks!
&gt; 
&gt; And my Order.xml list below:

Your configuration has serious problems. In particular, it appears all 
of the usual and necessary Processors that perform the steps of handling 
a single URI have been replaced by the Preselector processor.

I strongly recommend that you first perform a short crawl using the 
bundled default profile configuration, changing it only in the manner 
absolutely necessary to launch a crawl. (Add a suitable user-agent and 
from value.)

After confirming that works, you can make incremental changes to that 
configuration to achieve your alternate goals, testing to ensure each 
change has the desired effect and does not break the configuration.

The configuration of Heritrix is very flexible, and many components 
assume other standard components will be present in their usual 
arrangement. So, starting from scratch or making major changes without 
significant expertise is likely to result in broken crawls, while 
incremental changes from a working start will usually be safe.

Hope this helps,

- Gordon @ IA


